The paper deals with codes for cryptographic purposes and their behavior in network coding, which are topics related to information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the properties of linear codes (cs.CC) and their duality (cs.SI), as well as their application in network communication (cs.NI).
